  "prompt": "Where can I watch the first Fox News/Facebook 2016 Republican primary debate after it's over?",
  "response": "After the first Fox News/Facebook 2016 Republican primary debate, you can typically watch it through several platforms:\n\n1. **Fox News Website or App**: Fox News often provides clips and sometimes full replays of their debates on their official website or app. You may need to log in with a cable provider account to access the full content.\n\n2. **YouTube**: Fox News uploads segments or the full debate to their official YouTube channel. Search for the debate on YouTube to see if it\u2019s available.\n\n3. **Facebook**: Since the debate was co-hosted with Facebook, check the Fox News Facebook page or the debate-specific page for highlights or a full replay.\n\n4. **Cable/Satellite On-Demand Services**: If you have a cable or satellite subscription, you may be able to access the debate through your provider\u2019s on-demand service.\n\n5. **Streaming Services**: Some streaming services like Hulu Live, Sling TV, or YouTube TV may offer replays if they include Fox News in their channel lineup.\n\nIf you're looking for the debate long after it aired, your best bet might be YouTube or archived content on Fox News' website.",
